Anh - Anh
monotropy
[mə'nɒtrəpi]
■ noun Chemistry the existence of allotropes of an element, one of which is stable and the others metastable under all known conditions.
Derivatives
monotropenoun
Origin
early 20th cent.: from mono- + Gk tropē 'turning' + -y3.
